// EXPECT: 42
// WO-2 Lát A T3 (ADR-0065 §14.6, 2026-07-20): `Struct?` in RETURN position,
// PRESENT arm, BOTH fields read (`v.x + v.y`). Was a negative fixture
// pinning the temporary POLICY GATE (WO-StructReturnRefuse, 2026-07-19)
// shut; replaced by full-SRET for Copy-only `Struct?` return (ADR-0065
// §14). Pre-fix measured (§14.2): reading both fields traps SIGILL 132
// (garbage + garbage overflow, ADR-0044) — the loudest secondary symptom of
// the root "rác câm" (silent garbage) failure. EXPECT 42 (40+2) proves both
// fields land at the correct `{tag@0, fields@8+}` offsets.
struct P { x: Integer, y: Integer }

function make() -> P? {
    return ~+ P { x: 40, y: 2 };
}

function main() -> Integer {
    return match make() {
        ~+ v => v.x + v.y,
        ~0 => -1,
    };
}
